From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Georgi Davidkov <georgi.davidkov@tick42.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 12:33:32 +0300
Subject: fix: adjust client size constraints for frame insets before clamping

Cherry-pick of https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/7795073
  Chromium-Bug: 506480944
  Chromium-Commit: 22167afbecda05072355e5d8b324e00643b36bf4

Size constraints are given in client area coordinates when
WidgetSizeIsClientSize() is true. They need to be inflated by frame
insets before clamping the size of the HWND, otherwise the window
will be constrained to a smaller size than intended.

The inset correction was already present in OnGetMinMaxInfo. The CL
adds it to AdjustedContentBounds and SizeWindowToAspectRatio so they
handle constraints the same way when bounds change, and extracts the
duplicated arithmetic into a new helper InflateClientSizeConstraintsInPixels
in ui/views/win/hwnd_util.{h,cc}.

The unit test from the upstream CL (DesktopWidgetTest.SetBoundsRespectsMaximumSize)
is intentionally omitted: Electron does not run views_unittests.

SizeWindowToAspectRatio's inline inset block was previously added by
Electron's fix_aspect_ratio_with_max_size.patch (Cezary Kulakowski, 2021).
This commit refactors that inline block into the new helper call, matching
the upstream merged state. fix_aspect_ratio_with_max_size.patch remains in
place to preserve its other change (the SizeRectToAspectRatio API switch).

The helper extraction is included so that the follow-up patch
fix_use_adjustwindowrectexfordpi_for_dpi-consistent_frame_insets.patch
can layer cleanly on top.

diff --git a/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc b/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc
index 1c90d76572d365e1750129d23d5e59d651a46020..995085d4c87ca6517dc92cc487af3c9fc6277e6f 100644
--- a/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc
+++ b/ui/views/widget/desktop_aura/desktop_window_tree_host_win.cc
@@ -1537,6 +1537,17 @@ gfx::Rect DesktopWindowTreeHostWin::AdjustedContentBounds(
   gfx::Size maximum_size;
   GetMinMaxSize(&minimum_size, &maximum_size);
 
+  if (WidgetSizeIsClientSize()) {
+    // Constraints are sized to the client area, not the HWND (see
+    // OnGetMinMaxInfo), so inflate otherwise the max size will be too small.
+    display::win::ScreenWin* screen = display::win::GetScreenWin();
+    gfx::Size min_px = screen->DIPToScreenSize(GetHWND(), minimum_size);
+    gfx::Size max_px = screen->DIPToScreenSize(GetHWND(), maximum_size);
+    InflateClientSizeConstraintsInPixels(GetHWND(), min_px, max_px);
+    minimum_size = screen->ScreenToDIPSize(GetHWND(), min_px);
+    maximum_size = screen->ScreenToDIPSize(GetHWND(), max_px);
+  }
+
   gfx::Size bounds_size = bounds.size();
 
   if (!maximum_size.IsEmpty()) {
